f encouraging gender equality? As the title of this book suggests, the chapters provide an analysis of the broad trends - including changes and continuities - in the experiences, interests and concerns of Southeast Asian women. The chapters examine the trends related to women in the following arenas: the family, economic participation, politics, health, and religion. In some arenas, the trends reflect the disadvantages women face, which in turn have led to gender gaps; in other areas, women's progress has been found to eclipse that of the men, although this tends to be the exception.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aWomenzSoutheast AsiavCongresses. 0aWomen--Southeast Asia--Congresses. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBlackburn, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevasahayam, Theresa W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevasahayam, Theresa W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJones, Gavin W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKesavapany, K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohamad, Maznah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aResurreccion, Bernadette P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShoon, Yu-Foo Yee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShuib, Rashidah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z9783110606683